  <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" >

<head>
  <title>Java and HTML</title>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <script>
    function changeTitle(){
      var title = document.querySelector("#mainTitle");
      title.innerHTML += "<br>This new <u>title</u> has been changed from JavaScript!";
      title.style.color = 'black';
      title.style.backgroundColor = 'yellow';
      title.style.border = '5px dashed red';
      }
  </script>
</head>
  
<!--      <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css"> -->

  
<body>

<h1 id="mainTitle">My home page</h1>

  <p> This is an exmple of interactivity between JavaScript and the HTML content of a document." <button onclick="changeTitle();">Click me to change the title of the page</button></p>
  
  <p class="funny">Hi! Welcome to my Home Page! My name is Michel Buffa, I'm a professor at the University of Nice, in France, and I'm also the author of two MOOCS about HTML5 on W3Cx.</p>

  
